      "Visit to National Philatelic Museum, Science Museum and Shankar's International Dolls Museum",
    location: "Delhi and NCR",
    description:
      "Start your tour visiting National Philatelic Museum to enjoy rare collection of stamps, and also buy stamps from all over the world. Once here, also find special cancellations and firs-day covers to feel enriched. If scientific instruments of variety catch your fancy, head to the Science Museum, kids would like it. At the Shankar's International Dolls Museum, relish a staggering range of dolls from over 85 countries. A whopping 6,000 dolls are available here, richly dressed and carrying the traces of the region they belong. National Philatelic Museum (Sunday & Monday Closed) - This is a relatively an outlet for philatelists interested in Indian stamps, situated near Connaught Place. Science Museum (Monday Closed) - It was inaugurated on the 9th of January 1992 by the then Prime Minister of India. The National Science Centre, Delhi is a unit of the National Council of Science Museums (NCSM). Shankar's Doll Museum (Holi & Diwali Closed) -  Doll's Museum was set up by K. Shankar Pillai, a political cartoonist. The International Dolls Museum is a large collection of dolls in Delhi, India. National Philatelic Museum is closed on Saturdays, Sundays and national Holidays. National Science Centre and Dolls Museum is closed on Mondays and national Holidays.",
